revision.text:
==English==

===Etymology===
* {{suffix|accumulate|or}}. 
* From {{etyl|la|en}} {{term|lang=la|accumulator|accumulātor}}, agent noun of {{term|lang=la|accumulo|accumulō|pile up}}.

===Pronunciation===
* {{a|US}} {{IPA|/ə.ˈkjum.jə.ˌleɪ.tɚ/}}
* {{audio|en-us-accumulator.ogg|Audio (US)}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# One who, or that which, [[accumulate]]s.
#: ''He is a great '''accumulator''' of bad jokes.''
# {{context|British|lang=en}} A [[wet cell|wet-cell]] storage battery.
#: ''Looks like it's time to recharge the '''accumulator''' again.''
# {{context|betting|lang=en}} A collective [[bet]] on successive events, with both [[stake]] and [[winnings]] being carried forward to accumulate progressively.
# {{context|mechanics|lang=en}} A system of elastic springs for [[relieve|relieving]] the strain upon a rope, as in [[deep-sea]] [[dredging]].
# {{context|manufacturing|lang=en}} A vessel containing pressurized hot water ready for release as steam.
# {{context|engineering|hydraulics|lang=en}} A container which stores hydraulic power for release, in the form of a pressurized fluid (often suspended within a larger tank of fluid under pressure).
# {{context|computer science|lang=en}} A [[register]] in a calculator or computer used for holding the intermediate results of a [[computation]] or [[data]] [[transfer]].
# {{context|finance|lang=en}} A [[derivative]] contract under which the seller commits to sell shares of an underlying security at a certain [[strike price]], which the buyer is obligated to buy.

====Synonyms====
* {{sense|one who or that which accumulates}} [[collector]]
* {{sense|betting}} [[parlay]]
* {{sense|finance}} [[share forward accumulator]]
* {{sense|hydraulics}} [[shock absorber]]

